observations.recommendation:
We recommended to the Local Chief Executive to enjoin the following department heads’ compliance with the requirements in COA Circular 2015-008:

Require the Municipal Accountant the following reporting procedures:

Prepare the Journal Entry Voucher (JEV) to record the beginning balance of the local road network and its components in the general ledger and the LRNLCs, respectively; 

Support the JEV with the Registry of Public Infrastructures for Roads, working paper on the distribution of costs for the road components, and working paper on the determination of the depreciated replacement cost for road components with no available cost per registry;

Keep and maintain subsidiary records for roads and road components for every road network; and

Prepare a lapsing schedule for the computation of the depreciation for each component at the end of the year.

Instruct the Inventory Committee to conduct a physical count of all local road network and prepare and submit a RPCLRN to the Office of the Auditor on or before January 31 of each year;

Direct the Designated GSO to maintain the Local Road Inventory and Road Map, and to keep a complete LRNPC for all roads and its components; and

Direct the Municipal Engineer to provide the Municipal Accountant and Designated GSO with the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects.

Recommendations
We recommended to the Local Chief Executive to:
Require the Inventory Committee to prepare and submit a Physical Inventory Plan (PIP) and conduct a complete physical inventory count of all PPE and submit an updated and corrected RPCPPE in accordance with COA Circular No. 2020-006, dated January 31, 2020;
Relieve from any other functions the Designated GSO to properly perform her duties and responsibilities as a GSO and supply officer;
Instruct the Municipal Accountant and Designated GSO to prepare and maintain PPELC and PC, respectively, and reconcile the two records;
Direct the Municipal Accountant to implement the rules and regulations stated in COA Circular No.  2022-004 dated May 31, 2022 and COA Circular No. 2024-006 dated March 14, 2024 regarding the Semi-Expendable properties;
Instruct the Designated GSO/Supply Officer and the Municipal Accountant to regularly reconcile their records and review the composition of the PPE account to come up with an accurate classification of PPE account balance; and
The Municipal Accountant should review previous records to come up with the purchase amount of PPEs on the prior year’s.

