City Accountant to exert effort in the review of the entries in the PPEs SLs especially those with unreconciled /unidentified/ no detail balances and coordinate with the City General Services Officer for its reconciliation with property records and for possible derecognition of PPEs following the procedures laid down in COA Circular No. 2020-006 dated January 31, 2020;
General Services Officer to maintain complete duly accomplished and updated PCs to record all procurement and disposals of PPEs so that a reconciliation between the PCs with the physical count is possible; and
City Accountant and the General Services Officer to conduct periodic reconciliation of the accounting and property records as a result of the physical count, and make the necessary adjustments on any discrepancies noted, for accurate and fair presentation of PPE account balances in the financial statements.

We recommended and Management agreed that:

The AOs who are in custody of these unserviceable properties return these to the GSO through Property Return Slip for cancellation of ARE;
The General Services Officer cancel the corresponding ARE and include these unserviceable properties in the Inventory and Inspection Report of Unserviceable Property for disposal;
The Head of the Agency thru the General Services Officer file a request for appraisal of unserviceable properties for disposal to the COA Technical Team supported with necessary documents needed for technical evaluation and appraisal; and
The City Accountant prepare and record the necessary journal entries upon disposal of unserviceable PPEs and recognize any loss or gain on sale of PPE, if there is any.

We recommended that the City Mayor require the GSO to:

Fully update property card records especially on acquisitions and disposals, including unserviceable and items which cannot be located for reconciliation with Report on Physical Count, AREs, ICSs and with subsidiary ledgers maintained at the OCA; 

Conduct regular reconciliation with the OCA to ascertain the correctness of the PPE accounts balances and for fair financial statements presentation;
Maintain property cards on Land, Land Improvements, Buildings and Other Structures with complete data on acquisition/construction cost, appraised value, date and mode of acquisition for reconciliation with balances shown in the Subsidiary Ledgers maintained at the OCA; and

Prepare separate report on physical count of all tangible items below the capitalization threshold of ₱15,000.00 and issue Inventory Custodian Slip to persons responsible and accountable to establish accountability.

We further recommended that OCA should reclassify items below the capitalization threshold of ₱15,000.00 as semi-expendable inventory or expense accounts for fair presentation in the financial statements.

